(107, 3, '2018-03-07 03:29:06', '2018-03-07 03:29:06', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Scott’s career in public relations and marketing started in the nonprofit world, where he served as PR coordinator at the Austin-based headquarters of Special Olympics Texas. After SOTX, he led PR efforts at the world’s largest anti-fraud association before leaving to start his own PR consultancy. Scott is a partner at Patterson + Hughes, which has provided key support and sponsorship for nonprofit causes in Austin along with helping clients craft effective messages and connect with their audiences. </span>', 'Scott Patterson', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'scott-patterson', '', '', '2018-04-20 21:52:22', '2018-04-20 21:52:22', '', 0, 'http://tonyfoundation.wpengine.com/?post_type=tfpeople&#038;p=107', 0, 'tfpeople', '', 0),
(112, 3, '2018-03-07 03:38:43', '2018-03-07 03:38:43', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tony is a CPA licensed in the State of Florida.  Tony began his career in public accounting with Ernst &amp; Young (EY) performing financial statement audits for clients in several industries including capital markets and asset management, non-profit, health-care, and energy. Currently, Tony works in the digital and analytics arm of EYs Advisory Services where he focuses on the creation and implementation of new technologies to drive efficiency and provide greater insight both within EY and externally to clients.</span>', 'Tony Aguilar', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tony-aguilar', '', '', '2018-04-20 21:51:37', '2018-04-20 21:51:37', '', 0, 'http://tonyfoundation.wpengine.com/?post_type=tfpeople&#038;p=112', 0, 'tfpeople', '', 0),
(115, 3, '2018-03-07 20:00:17', '2018-03-07 20:00:17', 'Hailey is a business analyst and coder with a passion for information design. Her professional career began in a county hospital, where she worked alongside clinicians to collect and use injury data for improving patient care and public safety. She went on to manage ambulance and patient injury data programs for the State of California, co-founded <a href=\"https://codeforsacramento.org/\">Code for Sacramento,</a> and more recently, completed an 18-month civil service position as Open Data Analyst for the City of Austin.\r\n\r\nHailey is excited about her return to the health and wellness space through her work at Tony Foundation. As Director of Technology, she will design and deliver technology-based solutions that empower Tony, Scott, and all TF partners to support as many cancer-affected families as possible.', 'Hailey Pate', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hailey-pate', '', '', '2018-04-20 21:51:04', '2018-04-20 21:51:04', '', 0, 'http://tonyfoundation.wpengine.com/?post_type=tfpeople&#038;p=115', 0, 'tfpeople', '', 0),
(117, 3, '2018-03-07 03:42:48', '2018-03-07 03:42:48', 'Tim L. Laudadio is Chairman of Bell Environmental, Inc./ Bell Consulting, Inc. He founded the company over 22 years ago. He previously was an officer of three divisions of Browning-Ferris Industries (BFI) and was Senior Vice President of Texas Gulf Industries.\r\nTim has served on the board of several civic organizations &amp; youth baseball leagues. He is also active in his church. He is a resident of San Antonio.', 'Tim Laudadio', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tim-laudadio', '', '', '2018-03-09 20:44:52', '2018-03-09 20:44:52', '', 0, 'http://tonyfoundation.wpengine.com/?post_type=tfpeople&#038;p=117', 0, 'tfpeople', '', 0),
(119, 3, '2018-03-07 03:43:42', '2018-03-07 03:43:42', 'Scott has over a decade of extensive experience in financial operations, operational budgeting, due diligence, and financial analysis and modeling. He is currently the Executive Vice President of Asset Management for Core Spaces, where he oversees the management of company asset portfolios, performs financial analysis and reports on assets, and develops and implements strategies to increase the value of the company assets. Scott is a graduate of The University of Texas at Austin with a Bachelor of Science in Corporate Communications. He further received a MBA in Finance from St. Edward\'s University.', 'Scott Stager', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'scott-stager', '', '', '2018-03-09 20:44:20', '2018-03-09 20:44:20', '', 0, 'http://tonyfoundation.wpengine.com/?post_type=tfpeople&#038;p=119', 0, 'tfpeople', '', 0),
(120, 3, '2018-03-07 03:44:46', '2018-03-07 03:44:46', 'Kristine Laudadio Devine is a partner with the law firm of Harris Wiltshire &amp; Grannis where she provides regulatory and transactional counseling for telecommunications and technology companies. She lives in Austin with her husband Brian and their two kids, Clara and Jack.', 'Kristine Devine', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kristine-devine', '', '', '2018-03-09 20:40:38', '2018-03-09 20:40:38', '', 0, 'http://tonyfoundation.wpengine.com/?post_type=tfpeople&#038;p=120', 0, 'tfpeople', '', 0),
(121, 3, '2018-03-07 03:45:23', '2018-03-07 03:45:23', 'William is a tax attorney for the Texas Comptroller, and he is also a licensed CPA. He studied at Baylor University and the University of Texas. He loves traveling, reading, and playing golf.', 'William Hamner', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'william-hamner', '', '', '2018-03-29 02:36:38', '2018-03-29 02:36:38', '', 0, 'http://tonyfoundation.wpengine.com/?post_type=tfpeople&#038;p=121', 0, 'tfpeople', '', 0),
(123, 3, '2018-03-07 03:47:20', '2018-03-07 03:47:20', '<section id=\"about-us\" class=\"about-section\">\r\n<h1>Who We Are</h1>\r\nTony Foundation is a non-profit corporation based in Austin, Texas. We address critical needs for families in crisis due to cancer diagnosis. Our goal is to focus on meeting immediate, existing needs for families whose sole income earner, in their most productive years, has been diagnosed with cancer and is unable to continue employment.\r\n\r\nTo learn more about our strategy for supporting families impacted by cancer, read <a href=\"http://tonyfoundation.wpengine.com/our-journey-begins/\">Our Journey Begins</a>.\r\n\r\n</section><section id=\"tonys-story\" class=\"about-section\">\r\n<h1>Tony\'s Story</h1>\r\nMy name is Tony Laudadio, I am 34 with a wife and 3 daughters, and I have cancer. I was first diagnosed at age 29, in July of 2013, with renal cell carcinoma and a very large tumor. It caused me to lose my right kidney and forced me out of work for several months. I thought I was well on my way to recovery and potentially ringing the bell (sort of a fun cancer free ritual they do at MD Anderson) when I unexpectedly had my first two seizures. On September 24, 2015, I was diagnosed with a second, completely unrelated cancer -- brain cancer.\r\n\r\nAfter my docs determined I had Oligodendroglia Grade 3 Brain cancer, I underwent a successful \"awake craniotomy,\" which is a very specialized and rare surgery. It was about 8-10 hours long and I was awake for most of it. Following that, I underwent 30 days of brain radiation and 14 months of physical therapy and chemotherapy. Currently, my cancer is stable. But the fight we are facing is far from over and it will most likely be one that I battle for a long time.\r\n\r\nI feel like I have a great attitude and I think that is an absolute must. I have kindly been told that I am inspiring and brave and some other qualities, but honestly I am just trying to be like my role models were to me growing up. My grandparents and parents, my three siblings, my aunts and uncles, cousins, my close friends are all people who showed me how to get through tough times.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_124\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"227\"]<img class=\"wp-image-124 size-medium\" src=\"http://tonyfoundation.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/IMG_2208-e1520394646667-227x300.jpg\" alt=\"A picture of Tony\'s wife Carrie standing at the top of a hill with a picturesque background, wearing an \'I CAN fight cancer\' t-shirt.\" width=\"227\" height=\"300\" /> Tony\'s wife Carrie hiking in Tahoe[/caption]\r\n\r\nMost important of all, my wife, Carrie, has been my absolute rock through all of this. She was 7 months pregnant when they removed a tumor the size of a butternut squash from my kidney. Two years later, she was 8 months pregnant at MD Anderson when they operated on a large tumor in my brain. Her strength is remarkable.\r\n\r\nAnyone who knows Carrie definitely knows how true this is. She has been with me every step of the way and our love is stronger now than it has ever been. Throughout all of this, she has managed to provide structure at home with our kids, and she has been my biggest inspiration every day.\r\n\r\nFinally, I have always loved competition. I treat this experience like an adverse competitive situation, which is never something I have shied away from in the past. Anybody that knows me, knows that I live for those kind of moments. At times, cancer does test my resolve and patience, but I now use such a tough life issue to show my 3 daughters, my friends, and my family how to stare down adversity and continue to tell ‘em to \"bring it on.”\r\n\r\nThanks for reading my story. I hope that it might inspire you, or someone else you may be close with so please share it with others. I also encourage others to reach out for help if you need it.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nTony Laudadio\r\n<p class=\"tony-quote\">\"Worry is a terrible waste of the imagination.”\r\n<span class=\"tony-quote-author\">author unknown</span></p>\r\n\r\n</section><!--#tonys-story-->', 'About', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about', '', '', '2018-03-29 22:47:10', '2018-03-29 22:47:10', '', 0, 'http://tonyfoundation.wpengine.com/?post_type=tfcustompage&#038;p=123', 0, 'tfcustompage', '', 0),
