(289, 2, '2018-08-15 01:34:07', '2018-08-15 01:34:07', 'Cheyenne and Angela Streeter are great friends of Tony Foundation, and they hosted their own fundraising event with all proceeds benefiting our mission to help families affected by cancer. It was an awesome summer party complete with a dunk tank(!), games, swimming, delicious food, music and family fun. Check out this great video highlighting the event:\n\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEOAm_KAjSY[/embed]\n\n(Special thanks to Brian Dickman for another awesome video, and Missy Dickman for the great photos!)\n\nAfter the event, Cheyenne wrote the following letter to explain why he and Angela felt so strongly about holding a fundraiser for Tony Foundation:\n\n<em>I have known Tony for many years now and he and his family have become a big part of our lives. When we first heard of his first round of cancer we couldn’t believe it, and to then hear that after he beat it he then came down with a second. Words can’t express the way we felt!!!</em>\n\n<em>One thing we all know about Tony is he is probably the most positive person on the planet. Nothing is going to stop him from beating this terrible disease. Tony has managed to keep himself busy, whether it be continuing doing everything he did before to starting his foundation to help others.</em>\n\n<em>When Tony asked us to host a fundraiser at our house my answer was not yes, but \"heck\" yes! So, we immediately started planning. We wanted to have a relaxing event with all of our best friends and family. We made hamburgers, hot dogs, and had multiple sides brought in. The night before, the dunk tank was dropped off, which we had to try out (of course). Brett Curry donated multiple raffle items. James Delgado ran a 3-ball billiards tourney. Greg Rusnak ran a corn hole tourney. And of course, all the kids hung out in the pool all day. The event was a great success. I believe we were able to raise just under $4000 which is amazing!!! This money will go a long way towards helping out a family in need.</em>\n\n<em>I want to thank everyone that helped out and donated to help others and can’t wait for next year’s event!!!</em>\n\n<em>Thanks again,</em>\n\n<em>The Streeter Family</em>\n\nCheyenne and Angela, we can\'t thank YOU enough, and we can\'t wait for next year\'s event, either. The support of fundraisers like yours will help us support more families in crisis due to cancer.\n\nIf you would like to host an event, or know someone who would, please <a href=\"http://tonyfoundation.org/contact/\">contact us</a> today - we\'d love to discuss it with you. It might be something totally new, or an existing event that can help us in our mission to make a difference.\n\nSee some more great photos <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pg/tonyfoundation/photos/?tab=album&amp;album_id=2127210570896007\">here!</a>\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-285\" src=\"http://tonyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Streeter-pool-300x192.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"192\" />', 'Our Friends Make All the Difference', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '281-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-08-15 01:34:07', '2018-08-15 01:34:07', '', 281, 'http://tonyfoundation.org/281-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(291, 2, '2018-09-04 20:45:49', '2018-09-04 20:45:49', 'There can only be one. The first-ever Drive Away Cancer Golf Tournament has its first-ever Gold Sponsor: <a href=\"https://www.rebath.com/location/austin/\">Re-Bath of Austin.</a> We are honored to have their support!\r\n\r\nIt’s no surprise that such a community-oriented company like Re-Bath would step up to the tee box when it comes to helping families affected by cancer. “When they learned about our golf tournament, Re-Bath was very supportive of the cause,” said Tony Laudadio, founder of Tony Foundation. “They heard our story, and how it came about, and they asked how they could help.”\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-293 alignright\" src=\"http://tonyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/rebath2-300-for-blog-300x174.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"174\" />As the Gold Sponsor, Re-Bath is helping to underwrite the Sept. 28 tournament with a $2,500 contribution. The inaugural event is already a huge success, with 128 golfers set to tee off (in teams of four) at iconic Lions Municipal Golf Course in Austin.\r\n\r\nLaudadio said that Re-Bath is a great fit for the fundraiser – and for Austin. “Everyone knows that if you hire Re-Bath, they are the company that will come in and do a great bathroom model at a great price,” Laudadio said. “In fact, I’ve had a Re-Bath remodel, and so have many of my friends, and we’ve all been very happy with the results. But did you also know how much they support this community?\r\n\r\n“They’ve always been very community oriented, they give back in so many ways, and by helping support our mission, it just demonstrates how they put that commitment into action. We’re really thrilled to have their support.”\r\n\r\n<strong>A veteran-owned-and-operated business</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Austin location is one of more than 120 Re-Bath locations in the U.S., and it was founded in 2013 by Josh and Debra Agrelius. There are currently 23 full-time employees on the Re-Bath of Austin team – each is fully licensed and insured, and Re-Bath is even a state-licensed as a plumbing company. They can help make your bathroom more stylish or more accessible for the aging or disabled, and provide a complete bathroom remodel.\r\n\r\n<strong>A special thanks to all of our sponsors</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-294 alignright\" src=\"http://tonyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Tony-Lions-blog-300x192.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"192\" />The generosity of local businesses and individuals has helped make the first Drive Away Cancer tournament a success before a single ball has been struck. “We are overwhelmed and humbled by the support we’ve received, knowing that we’ll be able to help more families thanks to contributions from all of our sponsors.\r\n\r\nWhile there are still sponsorships available, we would like to thank those who have signed up already:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><u>Gold Sponsor</u></strong></h2>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.rebath.com/location/austin/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-340 size-full\" src=\"http://tonyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/rebath-small-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"171\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Re-Bath of Austin</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><u>Hole Sponsors</u></strong></h2>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.mccoys.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-321 size-full\" src=\"http://tonyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/McCoys_Logo_2C-small.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"182\" height=\"90\" /></a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>McCoy\'s Building Supply</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.bellenviro.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-341 size-full\" src=\"http://tonyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/bell-logo-small.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"140\" height=\"151\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Bell Env